items.text:
üé•** PAID CASTING CALL**

We are casting several roles for a series of short narrative pieces that highlight the stories of real families supported by our organization. These stories portray authenticity, warmth, and emotional depth.

**Location:** East Vancouver
**Audition Date:** October 20th

**Shooting Date:** October 23rd; must be available from 10-4 (you will not be needed the entire day)
**Compensation:** $200

**We are looking for actresses/actors to play: **

**Bruna**
* Female, late 20s to mid-40s
* Mother; caring and loving. Must convey determination, worry, and hope while navigating financial and emotional challenges for her children.

**Aisha**
* Female, early 30s to mid-40s
* Mother; warm, exhausted, and hopeful. Portrays a single parent managing multiple responsibilities with love and perseverance.

**Steven**
* Male, early 30s to mid-50s
* Father; provides care and guidance amid family hardship. Able to convey emotional strength and compassion.

**David**
* Male, mid-30s to 50s
* Father; supportive, patient, and empathetic. Represents the emotional toll of parenting through challenges while remaining steadfast for his family.

Please send a brief introduction and your headshot to **communications@ldsociety.ca. **We encourage applicants of all ethnicities and gender identities to apply.

Following auditions, we will confirm if you got the role and your timeslot via email on Tuesday, October 21st.

items.text:
UK/EU Actors seeking representation.

We are open to actors who do not have Spotlight (yet) and who are seeking representation in the UK/Europe. 

ANC is a brand new coop European agency. We are at the very early stages and still building our client list and relationships with casting and production. We are not yet on Spotlight which is why you don't need to be either.

If you are looking for your first agent feel free to email us.

- showreels
- professional headshots 
- filmmakers.eu and etalenta links (both are free to create)

Open to everyone above the age of 18+
Based in the UK or EU

- we do not charge any fees. 
- our commission is 10% from all work we secure.
- we are non-exclusive so, you free to look/have additional agents.

email: ancagency@hotmail.com

EDIT: 10/20 HAS BEEN FULLY LOCKED IN, BUT WE'RE STILL IN NEED OF FOLKD FOR 10/15 AND 10/24!

CASTING CALL

A new independent production company, Tu Bruja Productions, is casting Wilmington, NC-based background talent/extras for our upcoming project, ‚ÄúThe Return.‚Äù It‚Äôs a psychological/paranormal thriller centered on a haunted house. And we need a handful of extras for the following dates:

* **Overnight 10/15** - diners in a local Wilmington restaurant where we‚Äôll need up to 10 people to include in the background with a variety of ages. Call time would be 11 pm, and we would be wrapped well before 5:30 am on the 16th. Can arrive wearing casual clothing, but no logos, no green clothing, and no small prints to avoid camera ‚Äúbuzz‚Äù
* **Morning of 10/20** - office workers in a downtown Wilmington co-working space for about 4 hours with a prospective call time of 9 am to 1 pm. Ages 20- 65 would be great. Will need to arrive in business casual attire. 
* **Morning of 10/24** - need 4 to five people, couples and friend groups ages 18 - 50 are preferred to film at Miller‚Äôs Pond Park from 9 am to 12 pm. Can arrive wearing casual clothing, but no logos, no green clothing, and no small prints to avoid camera ‚Äúbuzz.‚Äù

It is a paid opportunity with a rate of $75/day for a one-day shoot with craft services available on set as well as film credit. 

If you‚Äôre interested and local to Wilmington, please email vvicenty@tubrujaproductions.com with your resum√©, headshot/selfie, and working contact number. Please don‚Äôt DM, as I can‚Äôt read FB message requests. Thanks in advance!

#paidopportunity #ISO #casting #wilmingtonnc #FilmCasting #horrormovie #psychologicalthriller

Hi guys, hope you‚Äôre all well. I have a question that I wanted to put out there to the collective as I don‚Äôt seem to be having much luck resolving it on my own.

I‚Äôm currently involved in various Acting workshops and I‚Äôm trying to find some kind of course (ideally a night course) that I could run alongside my full-time job.

I really want to properly learn Acting theory but other than degrees and postgraduate courses I‚Äôm struggling to find anything. Any suggestions no matter how left field would be greatly appreciated.

Thanks guys!
Matt.
items.title: Acting Academy | Professional Acting Classes and Training

topComments.text: Have a look at www.actingacademy.org it's run by Mark Pegg it's based online with inperson workshops. You don't it at your own speed and it will give you an all round of what you need for acting in front of the camera and stage  you really need to know it all. No need to audition either from Shakespeare to knowing what works on camera.
I'd also be interested in something like this. I live in East Midlands xx

items.text:
Chaos reigns in America.
A President who campaigned on bringing certainty to the country (i.e., ending the war in Ukraine before inauguration; ending inflation on day 1; restoring the country‚Äôs image in the world; restoring free speech in the nation) has achieved none of these promises. Quite to the contrary.
But what if this chaos we‚Äôre experiencing is not a by-product of Donald Trump‚Äôs policies? What if chaos is his sole goal? The ultimate distraction from a plan to drive the country toward his consolidation of power; and away from the protections of a free society and a court system sworn to the rule of law.

Could I have imagined waking up one morning and finding a U.S. President has ordered troops to police streets across the country. The rationale keeps changing from protecting ICE agents that are tracking down immigrants ‚Äúbased on looking Latin or having brown skin,‚Äù to stopping the horrendous crime going on in cities which major independent research sources report is actually down 30-40%.
After six decades of a Republican party arguing for primacy of state action vs federal interference, there is deafening silence in the face autocratic rule.

Are these actions being taken to create the very chaos and revulsion from law abiding citizens you‚Äôd expect in a free society?   Nothing here is being done collaboratively with State Governors, local police forces.

Like my neighbors, I watched in shock as President Trump told top U.S. generals described anyone who opposes his policies as ‚Äúthe enemy from within.‚Äù  Trump field-tested his plan to send armed troops under the guise of policing U.S. citizens, because of the chaos he‚Äôs creating.
The violence and death of law enforcement officers on Jan 6 is now a blood stained footnote in history, but rioters convicted in a court of law have now been pardoned.
Trump asked the nation to give him ‚Äúone party‚Äù majorities so he could implement his vision for the country has done nothing of what he promised. Tariffs are forcing a return of inflation and rising prices; job growth has slowed ‚Äì and the power sought to improve the lives of average Americans has caused economic uncertainty and chaos.
After ten years of trying to destroy Obamacare, Republicans now would gut this vital health insurance program to deny 20-25 million Americans their health coverage.  President Trump and Republicans in Congress knew the cutting healthcare insurance would force a government shut down.

There is a plan afoot for what we‚Äôre experiencing. Our only hope is connecting the dots and restraining the long term damage being caused to our economy, our values and our standing in the world.

I want my grandchildren to grow up knowing I did not sit on the sidelines, in response to this existential threat.  "Neutrality helps the oppressor, never the victim. Silence encourages the tormentor, never the tormented." E Weisel.

**NOW CASTING:** Parents of kids aged 2-12 living in California for a *Brightlife Kids *digital Campaign! 

**Rate:** $500 

**Usage:** Inperp/worldwide 

Parents remember a simpler childhood with fewer screens and more freedom, but raising kids now means navigating new, complex challenges: the constant buzz of technology, the pressures of social media, and a rising cost of living. You‚Äôll ask a question and our Brightlife Kid Coach will help parents navigate tough situations. 

**Role 1**: Toddler Parent (3-5yrs old) questions about how to help a toddler express anger. 

**Role 2**: Tween Parent (10-12yrs old) questions about social media use. 

**Role 3:** School aged parent (5-13yrs old) questions about separation anxiety 

Please submit a selftape (no more than 30 seconds) to *lsteinberg@attn.com* introducing yourself, your child(ren) age(s) and why you need help. 

If you are comfortable filming in kids room this is a WFH opportunity (please note in email).

items.text:
Casting Call: NEWSREADER

Looking to cast an actor (male or female) to play a newsreader for a corporate training video. 

- playing age 35-55
- Men and women of all ethnicities open to apply
- Natural US accent preferred but British RP also potentially an option
- Will need to supply your own wardrobe which must be an appropriate formal outfit for a tv newsreader

The film recreates a breaking news segment from an American news channel so we are seeking someone who can emulate the slick professional CNN newsanchor style of presenters like Anderson Cooper and Jake Tapper.

The job involves reading two short scripts from an autocue. Our filming time is limited so please only apply if you have some experience reading from autocue - this is not the job to have your first crack at trying it!

Fee: ¬£125 for approx. 2 hours of shooting time on location in a central London office.

Shoot is likely to be Wednesday or Thursday this week (22nd/23rd October)

Please send headshots/spotlight profile along with any relevant work examples to me at Hello@jonfairey.co.uk and detail any experience in similar roles. No DMs here please.

topComments.text: Emailed. I work in TV news.

üêõCasting Call üêõ
Super excited to announce our upcoming short film ‚ÄúCaterpillar‚Äù 

Please see the link for the application pack. 

We are looking for a Manchester based male actor with a playing age 17 - 23 to play one of the lead roles. 

This is a passion project so unfortunately this role is UNPAID. 

However this is an opportunity to work with an experienced up and coming team, with shorts already playing at BAFTA and BIFA qualifying festivals, to have footage for showreel and potential festival screenings. 

To apply please email the following to our producer India indiarainmedia@gmail.com, director Chey cheyennechristiecontent@gmail.com and Amy  amylever2000@gmail.com : 
 
1) A headshot
2) A brief summary of previous work and interest in the role. 
3)Your age 
4) A link to your spotlight profile / CV.
5)Your base 
6) Availability 

Deadline : October 27th 5pm

Please be aware this is a low budget short so we will be prioritising Manchester based talent.

We are hoping to film a proof of concept at the end of November with the provisional date of November 26th. We are hoping to shoot the short Spring 2026.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bliEA9aeNvZWR2WxKnnz6RPcf9G3D7QNAfFJtFq2Naw/edit?usp=drivesdk

4) A link to your spotlight profile / CV.
5)Your base 
6) Availability 

Deadline : October 27th 5pm

Please be aware this is a low budget short so we will be prioritising Manchester based talent.

We are hoping to film a proof of concept at the end of November with the provisional date of November 26th. We are hoping to shoot the short Spring 2026.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bliEA9aeNvZWR2WxKnnz6RPcf9G3D7QNAfFJtFq2Naw/edit?usp=drivesdk

I hope this is ok to post and please share with anyone who may benefit from this.

5 day free challenge Tame Your Inner Critic so that you can perform with more self-trust & freedom. Sign up to receive a link to daily challenge exercises.

 

Join my FREE 5-day ‚ÄòTame Your Inner Critic‚Äô challenge.

Stop the self-sabotage and start performing with self-trust.

 

That voice that picks apart your performance, tells you you're a fraud, and magnifies every tiny mistake? It's the biggest dream-killer for performers.

 

I'm Dr Maja Jankowska, a Clinical Psychologist specialising in the mental health of stage performers. I help artists silence their true biggest critic - the one inside their head.

 

This free challenge gives you the psychological tools to transform that harsh inner narrator from a saboteur into a manageable & helpful stagehand. We will learn the steps to trade pre-show panic and post-show post-mortem for focused confidence and self trust.

 

In 5 days, you will learn how to:

IDENTIFY your critic's unique triggers and tactics (give it a name and neutralise its power).

INTERRUPT its automatic, harsh commentary with a simple 'catch-and-reframe' technique.

CREATE a more balanced and compassionate inner dialogue.

PERFORM with more creative freedom and self-trust, because you're no longer your own worst enemy.

 

The challenge starts on 27th October.

 

The goal isn't to never have a critical thought again. It's to stop that thought from running the show.

Ready to trade self-sabotage for self-leadership?

 

Click the link below or scan a QR code to sign up.

[https://bit.ly/3KPB9z9](https://bit.ly/3KPB9z9)

# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane‚Äôs resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could‚Äôve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a ‚ÄúKaren Carpenter‚Äù fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s‚Äì80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional ‚Äî a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film‚Äôs psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40‚Äì85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control ‚Äî much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**

ATTENTION WARSAW AND SURROUNDINGS!!!
On October 29th and 30th for commercial for a well-known brand, we're looking for woman and men of Asian and Afro-American origin aged 25-35 as episodic actors.

The rate is PLN 1000 net per day of shooting.

Please send applications with the note ADVERTISING containing your name and surname, a current face photo and a photo of your silhouette and your phone number to the email:
mkmstudio@mkmstudiofilm.pl

We will contact the selected people by phone.

You are cordially invited!
MKM Studio Crew

items.text:
Casting Call: The Chaos

We are seeking talented and passionate actors (18+) to join our exciting new Indie project! This is a unique opportunity to be part of a creative and collaborative production, utilizing **virtual production techniques** and **green screen technology**.

Requirements:

- Must be 18 years or older

- Comfortable performing in front of a green screen

- Enthusiastic about participating in an indie, creative-driven environment

Details:

- This is an unpaid project, but it offers a great chance to build your portfolio and gain experience in virtual production.

- Flexible scheduling for green screen scenes.

- A fantastic opportunity to work with a dedicated team on a passion project.

-IMDb Credit

If you're excited to bring unique characters to life in an innovative way, we'd love to hear from you!

To Apply:

Please submit a headshot, resume, and a brief video introduction.

They do not have to be professional!

We are looking for someone to portray these characters!

More information will be given after submission:

Chris presents himself as calm, confident, and even comforting. His tone is measured ‚Äî he doesn‚Äôt command; he invites. He speaks like a leader or preacher, someone used to controlling a room through subtle persuasion rather than force. The steady eyes, careful pouring, and soft assurances suggest someone who knows how to perform sincerity.

Underneath the calm surface, there‚Äôs a manipulative intent.

Chris Myers (African American ages 20-30)

‚ú®CASTING IS LIVE! ‚ú®

Between Acts is looking for singers in the North-West to audition for our first ever cabaret evening! 

The theme is 'Miscast' so it will be songs paired with unlikely people. We ask that you fill out our audition form (found in the link below), send in a 2 minute self tape and the deadline to apply is the 9th of November.

All the information is here and we'll be releasing an FAQ video soon to answer some more questions but, if you do have any questions, follow the contact info or our link-tree below!

Come and join us, we can‚Äôt wait to meet you üåü

items.text:
Mickey Mouse Horror Short Film
Hello, I am currently producing a Mickey Mouse Short film, with the working title, The Mouse Killer, which may become the actual title. 

This film is apart of my two existing films, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 1 and 2. This serves as the next chapter within the series, that will lead into the 3rd and final My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh film. 

Film Synopsis: two women are out in the woods, hunting down a mythical creature known as, Steamboat Willie, or Willie. 

If it all works out, this short film will be the start of a trilogy of short films. With the final one leading up to My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 3.

Actors Age Range: 21 to up.

Looking for two females who can play the roles.

Compensation: none

Location: Fort Collins Colorado 

If you're interested, send me a message!

Hello, Everyone I‚Äôm Vosiey Fvogueswier a inspiring entertainer and career consultant! I wanted to take the time to invite you to our entrepreneurship program with Road 2 Stardom Productions L.L.C, helping entertainers/entrepreneurs advance their careers in the entertainment industry, also helping grow their brand/label while advancing their knowledge and exposure in the industry. üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

üé¨ CASTING CALL - Holiday Commercial üéÑ

Non-Union | Paid Roles | Denver Area

We're casting a heartwarming 1970s nostalgia-themed holiday commercial for a property management company.

SHOOT DATE: November 9, 2025
LOCATION: Denver Area, Colorado
SUBMISSION DEADLINE: Friday, October 24th

USAGE: Full buyout

ROLES AVAILABLE:

CHILD (Male, 7-10) - SPEAKING ROLE - $700/day
Lead role! Looking for a talented young actor who can deliver genuine Christmas morning excitement. Must submit reel showing previous work. This is a standout role perfect for your reel!

ADULT LANDLORD (Male, 45-55) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day 

Plays grown-up version of Child. Warm, relatable, trustworthy presence. Reel or work samples required.

MOM (Female, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Supportive, amused mom in 1970s Christmas scene. Natural reactions, expressive warmth. Reel or work samples required.

DAD (Male, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Bemused but proud dad, possibly behind camera with VHS camcorder. Reel or work samples required.

SISTER (Female, 5-12) -  NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Natural younger sibling for Christmas morning scene. Great opportunity for younger talent!

-Meals provided on set
-Professional production environment
-Copy of final commercial for your reel (after release)

LOCAL HIRE ONLY - No travel or lodging provided

TO SUBMIT:

Please email video reel showing your acting talent, plus a headshot to:

[CollectiveCp.Casting@gmail.com](mailto:CollectiveCp.Casting@gmail.com) 

EMAIL SUBMISSIONS ONLY please. 

Thank you for your interest!!

Grandfather 55-70 years old, all races, healthy body type

F√ºr meinen kommenden Kurzfilm ‚ÄûZwischen Licht und Schatten‚Äú (Drehort gebe ich noch bekannt) am 10.01 und 11.01 suche ich noch engagierte Mitwirkende:

üé¨ Regie

Ich suche eine/n Regisseur:in, die/der Lust hat, gemeinsam mit mir diesen emotional intensiven Kurzfilm umzusetzen. Das Projekt ist charaktergetrieben und bewegt sich zwischen innerem Konflikt, famili√§rer Bindung und Selbstfindung.

Erfahrung ist w√ºnschenswert, aber kein Muss ‚Äî wichtiger ist Leidenschaft, Teamgeist und Gesp√ºr f√ºr authentisches Schauspiel.

üé≠ Rollen

üë©‚Äçü¶∞ Lucy (ca. 25‚Äì28 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas beste Freundin

‚Äì herzlich, empathisch, gute Zuh√∂rerin

‚Äì ruhig, aber pr√§sent, gibt Stella Halt

‚Äì Spielalter: ca. 26 Jahre

‚Äì Drehtage: [1‚Äì2]

‚Äì Keine Gage, aber Verpflegung + Material f√ºr Showreel

üë¶ Felix (Spielalter 20-22 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas j√ºngerer Bruder

‚Äì ehemals drogenabh√§ngig, heute sehr zur√ºckhaltend, manchmal verschlossen

‚Äì steht im Zwiespalt zwischen Angst und St√§rke

‚Äì hat Respekt vor Viktor (dem B√∂sewicht , drogendealer), aber kann sich im entscheidenden Moment behaupten

‚Äì Drehtage: 10.01-11.01

Kurzinhalt

Die 25-j√§hrige Stella lebt zur√ºckgezogen, misstrauisch gegen√ºber M√§nnern und misstrauisch

gegen√ºber Gef√ºhlen. Als sie im Park den sportlichen, offenen Nick kennenlernt, entsteht eine

leise N√§he ‚Äì doch Stella blockt jeden Ann√§herungsversuch ab.

W√§hrend sie langsam Vertrauen zu Nick fasst, ger√§t ihr Bruder Felix in ernste Schwierigkeiten:

Er schuldet Victor, einem gef√§hrlichen Drogendealer, 5.000 Euro. Victor bedroht Felix und sucht

schlie√ülich auch Stella auf, um an sein Geld zu kommen.

Eines Abends eskaliert die Situation. Victor lauert Stella auf ‚Äì und als Nick hinzukommt, versucht

er, sie zu sch√ºtzen. Er h√§lt ihm sein Portemonnaie mit 300 Euro hin, um Zeit zu gewinnen. Doch

Victor wird w√ºtend: ‚ÄûIch will mein Geld ‚Äì oder einer von euch stirbt!‚Äú

Nick sagt zu Stella, sie solle laufen. Zitternd flieht sie und versteckt sich hinter einem Baum.

Dann kommt es zum Kampf zwischen Nick und Victor. In einem verzweifelten Moment wird

Victor im Bauch verletzt und bricht zusammen. Als Stille einkehrt, tritt Stella hervor, ruft ‚ÄûNick!‚Äú,

l√§uft zu ihm, und beide fallen sich unter Tr√§nen in die Arme. Ein Moment zwischen Dunkelheit

und Hoffnung ‚Äì und vielleicht der Beginn einer echten Heilung.

Drehtort noch unbekannt Max im Umkreis von 200 km  von Nordhorn

üóìÔ∏è Drehzeitraum: Januar 2026

üí¨  ‚Äì gern per PN oder E-Mail an [de.pascalis1990@web.de] kontaktieren

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì BOULDER, CO**
**Shoot Date:** Saturday, October 26 (6 days away)
**Project:** *Under My Eyelids* ‚Äì a heartfelt short film about an ex professional skateboarder reflecting on his memories of skateboarding after a severe TBI.

**ROLE:** Kid Cody (Boy, 9‚Äì11)
‚Äì Curious, brave, and a little shy.
‚Äì Comfortable standing or riding on a skateboard (no tricks required).
‚Äì Appears in an emotional flashback scene with his mom at a skatepark.

**LOCATION:** Boulder / Louisville area skatepark
**TIME:** Half-day shoot (3‚Äì5 hours)
**COMPENSATION:** Non-paid. Food, credit, and footage for reel will be provided.

**TO APPLY:**
Email **baxterdylan7@gmail.com** or call/text **(**970)406-2336 with:
‚Äì Child‚Äôs name and age
‚Äì Recent photo
‚Äì Parent/guardian contact information
‚Äì Any skateboard experience

This is a warm, character-driven scene about facing fear and finding courage.
‚Äî Dylan Lee Baxter
Writer / Director, *Under My Eyelids*

Dream Social ‚Äì Remote (Contract)

Pay: $25/hour | Hours: 3‚Äì5 per week

About Dream Social

Dream Social helps creators who want to stream full-time grow, monetize, and build sustainable income through TikTok LIVE. We‚Äôre a fast-growing TikTok creator agency working with streamers all over the world , and we‚Äôre looking for a confident, camera-ready recruiter to join our team!

About the Role

As a TikTok Livestream Recruiter, you‚Äôll host livestreams directly from the Dream Social company TikTok account, connecting with potential creators who are interested in joining our agency.

You‚Äôll represent the brand on camera, explain how Dream Social helps streamers grow, answer live questions, and encourage viewers to apply.

This role is perfect for someone who loves TikTok LIVE, feels natural engaging with people on camera, and enjoys motivating others to take action.

What You‚Äôll Do

    ‚Ä¢    Go LIVE on the Dream Social TikTok account for 3‚Äì5 hours each week (in one-hour sessions)

    ‚Ä¢    Engage with viewers in real time ‚Äî answer questions, build excitement, and guide them through applying

    ‚Ä¢    Represent the Dream Social brand with positivity and professionalism

    ‚Ä¢    Follow provided scripts, content guidelines, and examples from other recruiters

    ‚Ä¢    Track livestream engagement and report back feedback or common viewer questions

What We‚Äôre Looking For

    ‚Ä¢    Confident and comfortable speaking on camera

    ‚Ä¢    Familiar with TikTok LIVE and how it works

    ‚Ä¢    Has hosted or streamed on TikTok LIVE at least once

    ‚Ä¢    Energetic, clear communicator who can connect with an audience

    ‚Ä¢    Reliable, consistent, and excited to be part of a creative, growing team

Schedule & Pay

    ‚Ä¢    Pay: $25/hour (contractor role)

    ‚Ä¢    Hours: 3‚Äì5 hours per week

    ‚Ä¢    Schedule: Fixed livestream times that fit around your availability

Training Provided

You‚Äôll receive full onboarding, training, and access to past livestreams from other recruiters so you can learn exactly what works.

How to Apply

Apply directly through Indeed with your resume. In the ‚ÄúMessage to Employer‚Äù section, please also include:

    1.    Your TikTok handle

    2.    Your phone number

    3.    Where you‚Äôre based (city/state)

    4.    Your knowledge of TikTok LIVE (1‚Äì10)

    5.    Whether you know what a TikTok Creator Network does
